<div class="row p-3 gap-3 flex-column flex-md-row">
  <div class='p-0 my-1 fw-bold'>Copyright and permission to publish</div>
  <div class='my-1'>
    In addition to appropriately citing materials, the user will comply with copyright law (Title 17, U.S. Code). 
    Permission of the copyright hlder may be required for use, publication (including posting materials on publicly 
    available websites), or reproduction. Useres acknowledge that they are solely responsible for determining
    the copyright status of the materials they use and for obtaining any necessary permissions from the
    copyright owner
  </div>
  <div class='my-1'>
    The user agrees to indemnify Stanford University from any claim relating to the publication of
    materials from the Stanford University Libraries.
  </div>
  <div class='p-0 my-1 fw-bold'>Photography</div>
  <div class='my-1'>
    Photography of collections is generally permitted. Permissions, practices, and equipment allowances
    may vary by reading room and collection. Please consult the reading room staff for further information.
  </div>
  <div class='p-0 my-1 fw-bold'>Reproduction requests</div>
  <div class='my-1'>
    Digitization requests will be mediated through reading room staff. Some digitization requests may be 
    completed at a cost to the researcher, while others may be provided free of charge. More information can be found on the
    policy page for each reading room (linked above).
  </div>
  <div class='my-1'>
    The libraries reserve the right to review materials before a digital copy is made (including scans, digital copies,
    and photographs) and the right to deny a digitization request.
  </div>
  <div class='my-1 p-3 terms-agree'>
          <%= check_box_tag "aeon_terms", 'agree', required: true, id: "aeon_terms" %>
          <%= label_tag "aeon_terms", 'I agree to these terms', class:'fw-bold redesign-required-label' %>
          <br/>
          By checking this box, you acknowledge and agree to comply with the policies and regulations above.
  </div>
</div>
